&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.greenhouse.com/mission&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;mission&lt;/a&gt; at Greenhouse is to make every company great at hiring – so we go to great lengths to hire great people because we believe that they’re the foundation of our success. At Greenhouse, you’ll join a team that collaborates purposefully, fosters inclusivity, and communicates with transparency and accountability so we can help companies measurably improve the way they hire.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us to do the best work of your career, solving meaningful problems with remarkable teams.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Greenhouse is looking for a&lt;strong&gt; Partner Manager, Private Equity &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Partner Manager will be responsible for building and growing indirect sales with private equity partners. They will lead and manage all aspects of the partnership, including recruitment, product enablement, marketing sponsorships (in collaboration with our marketing team), and helping shepherd portfolio companies through our sales cycle with sales and account management teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience in driving new business and adoption through private equity firms. You will be someone with a growth mindset and a positive attitude who sees challenges as opportunities and has the ability to motivate and lead by example.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who will love this job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A business developer&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp; An excellent communicator and relationship builder with strong business acumen. Experienced with business development practices that result in revenue, including partner recruitment/pitching and strategic partner account management.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A collaborator &lt;/strong&gt;- Demonstrated experience working with Sales, Account Management, and Marketing teams. You have a strong understanding of co-marketing activities and a track record of collaborating with marketers to drive leads and enhance brand visibility through channel partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A results-driven individual &lt;/strong&gt;- Focused on achieving measurable outcomes and surpassing targets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own strategic private equity partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with PE partners to strengthen the mutual value of the partnership and drive partner-sourced revenue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify partner marketing opportunities and work closely with Marketing to ensure successful execution and results&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, coordinate, and execute presentations to inform, persuade, educate, and ultimately source referrals from the partner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the Greenhouse platform and be prepared to answer questions to help partners identify referral opportunities from their portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive urgency within partners, working closely through sales cycles from targeting accounts for pipeline generation to influencing customer renewals&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel occasionally to industry conferences and partner meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional projects and responsibilities as business needs require&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and/or managing a private equity partner channel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience managing partner relationships within SaaS technology partners resulting in measured partner-sourced revenue&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with mid-market and/or enterprise partners, customer-facing teams (sales, sales engineering, customer success), and customers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience successfully influencing stakeholders of varied levels and motivations within partner organizations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience executing partner marketing initiatives in collaboration with Marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your own unique talents! Your background has given you a unique perspective and set of transferable skills that aren&#39;t always in alignment with a given role - but those are qualities we value at Greenhouse. If you don&#39;t meet 100% of the qualifications outlined above, we still strongly encourage you to apply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Applicants must be currently authorized to work in the United States on a full-time basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you are based in California, we encourage you to read this important information for California residents linked&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.greenhouse.io/ccpa-candidate&quot;&gt; &lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;here&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The national pay range for this role is $119,000.00 - $167,000.00. Individual compensation will be commensurate with the candidate&#39;s experience and qualifications. Certain roles may be eligible for additional compensation, including stock option awards, bonuses, and merit increases. Additionally, certain roles have the opportunity to receive sales commissions that are based on the terms of the sales commission plan applicable to the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenhouse provides a variety of benefits to employees, including medical, dental, and vision insurance, basic life insurance, mental health resources, financial wellness benefits, and a fully paid parental leave program. For US-based employees, we offer short-term and long-term disability coverage, a 401(k) plan and company match. U.S. based employees also receive, per calendar year, up to 14 scheduled paid holidays and up to 80 hours of paid sick leave. Non-exempt employees accrue up to 20-25 days of paid vacation time annually, depending on tenure, and exempt employees have flexible paid time off (PTO).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The anticipated closing date for this role is &lt;strong&gt;Monday, December 22, 2025.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;#LI-BB2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Greenhouse, we live by our mission through &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.greenhouse.com/interviewing-at-greenhouse&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;using our own product&lt;/a&gt; to help us hire the right person for the job, every time. We are a remote-first company and have shared office spaces in New York City and Ireland, and optional co-working spaces that give us flexibility to do our best work anywhere. We take an active role in our growth through a performance review program that’s committed to providing actionable feedback, and a bonus structure that rewards great performance. We believe that bringing together a variety of perspectives makes us a stronger company – and we nurture leaders who create an inclusive culture and invest into employee resource groups that celebrate our differences and life experiences. We’re proud to have built an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.greenhouse.com/awards&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;award-winning culture&lt;/a&gt; that’s been recognized as Fortune’s Best Places to Work and Inc.’s Best Workplaces multiple years in a row.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
